The paper deals with supervised topic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning. The paper proposes improvements to the existing logistic supervised topic models by introducing a regularization constant and developing a simple Gibbs sampling algorithm. These improvements are expected to improve prediction performance and time efficiency. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
